  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Development for Putumayo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Stregthen Condimentos Putumayo and its 60 producers as an organization in administration, marketing and commercialization to increase it income and sustainability.

2. Improve the systems of pepper production on 120 farms with a plan of land tenure security, management of crops based on the Best Agricultural Practices and trainings in sustainable agriculture. 

3. Improve the overall wellbeing of 2,425 pepper-producing families and vulnerable communities with a special focus on the development of youth, protection, gender and conflict victims</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Development of Putumayo will work in three sectors&#x2014;children &amp;amp; youth, food security and sustainable community development&#x2014;primarily with the a 60 pepper-producing families who make up Condimentos Putumayo. The project will create alliances with local and regional authorities to include at-risk populations located in resource rich areas of Colombia.</narrative>
  </description>
